  "learn": [
    {
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Sharing Into 8 Equal Groups",
      "content": "When you divide by 8, you share a total equally among 8 groups. Example: 48 counters shared into 8 groups → each group gets 6. So 48 ÷ 8 = 6.",
      "id": "LN_01",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "counter_groups",
        "config": {
          "total": 48,
          "groups": 8,
          "per_group": 6
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Halve Three Times Strategy",
      "content": "Dividing by 8 is the same as halving three times (because 8 = 2×2×2). Example: 24 ÷ 8\nStep 1: 24 ÷ 2 = 12\nStep 2: 12 ÷ 2 = 6\nStep 3: 6 ÷ 2 = 3\nResult: 24 ÷ 8 = 3. Check: 8 × 3 = 24 ✓",
      "id": "LN_02",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "diagram",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "three_step_halve",
        "config": {
          "start": 24,
          "step1": 12,
          "step2": 6,
          "step3": 3
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Array: 8 Rows",
      "content": "A 8×9 array has 72 tiles arranged in 8 rows of 9. Reading it as division: 72 tiles in 8 rows means 72 ÷ 8 = 9 tiles per row. The ×8 fact 8×9=72 gives the ÷8 fact 72÷8=9.",
      "id": "LN_03",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "array_grid",
        "config": {
          "rows": 8,
          "cols": 9
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Number Line: Backward Jumps of 8",
      "content": "To find 72 ÷ 8, start at 72 on a number line and hop backward by 8 each time: 72 → 64 → 56 → 48 → 40 → 32 → 24 → 16 → 8 → 0. Count the hops: 9 hops. So 72 ÷ 8 = 9.",
      "id": "LN_04",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "number_line",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "number_line",
        "config": {
          "start": 72,
          "end": 0,
          "jump": -8,
          "label": "72 ÷ 8 = 9 hops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "The ÷8 Pattern: Reverse the ×8 Fact",
      "content": "Every ×8 fact gives you a ÷8 fact:\n8×1=8 → 8÷8=1\n8×2=16 → 16÷8=2\n8×3=24 → 24÷8=3\n8×4=32 → 32÷8=4\n8×5=40 → 40÷8=5\n8×6=48 → 48÷8=6\n8×7=56 → 56÷8=7\n8×8=64 → 64÷8=8\n8×9=72 → 72÷8=9\n8×10=80 → 80÷8=10\nStrategy: think '8 × ? = dividend' to find the quotient.",
      "id": "LN_05",
      "cpa_phase": "abstract",
      "visual_type": "table",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "fact_table",
        "config": {
          "divisor": 8,
          "range": [
            1,
            10
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ],
